Naming Conventions:

Naming conventions makes code more readble.

Java Follows Camel Casing Rule -MyFirstJavaClass.   

Second Word first letter should be Capital.

ClassName:

Always use Class name very specific to the Project you are working.

It should have Noun like Student, Engineer.First letter should be Capital

Variable Name:

Always Use Variable Names very specific to the Projects you are Working.variables should be Small letters.

Example:

StudentName - sname;
PhoneNumber - phno

Method:

abc()
main()

Small letetrs.
Interface:

Most of the Interface should have 'able' at the end.

Runable
Serizable
Remote

Constant:

PI, DENSITY.  All letter should be CAPITALS